      <prop type="x-chinese-ref">易經 27 六四</prop>
      <prop type="x-translation-ref">易經 27 六四</prop>
      <tuv xml:lang="zh-Hant">
        <seg>六四：顛頤吉，虎視眈眈，其欲逐逐，无咎。</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv xml:lang="en">
        <seg>The fourth SIX, divided, shows one looking downwards for (the power to) nourish. There will be good fortune. Looking with a tiger's downward unwavering glare, and with his desire that impels him to spring after spring, he will fall into no error.</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
